She turned and faced the doorway, wondering if her leader or second in 
command would enter through it.  She thought about how Quickstrike made her 
feel earlier.  She wondered if she could have her programmming changed so 
she would not feel this way.  Something about him made her feel 
uncomfortable.  Like she owed him something.  Like she was supposed to pay 
him back for something.  And yet she could not think of what it was.  She 
kind of liked him. And at the same time, she feared him. She started to 
smile at the thought of him standing there talking to the other bot. She 
shook her head.  She knew that getting close ment getting hurt. But 
something about him drove her logic circuits crazy. He also put butterflies 
in her stomach.  Why the hech should she even care.  He was the second in 
command.  He could have any female bot he wanted.  Yet, she had this 
overwhelming urge just to want to talk to him. What was wrong with her, she 
thought.
